Serena Williams Fined $2,000 After Outburst During U.S. Open Tennis Loss

-- B y   M a s o n   L e v i n s o n
-- 
2011-09-12T18:39:43Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-12/serena-williams-fined-2-000-after-outburst-during-u-s-open-tennis-loss.html
Serena Williams  was fined $2,000
for verbally abusing the chair umpire during her loss to
Samantha Stosur in the U.S. Open women’s final.  The U.S. Tennis Association announced the fine in a
statement, less than two hours before  Rafael Nadal  and Novak Djokovic were scheduled to play the men’s final of the Grand
Slam tournament at the National Tennis Center in  New York .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mason Levinson in New York at 
 mlevinson@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Sillup at   msillup@bloomberg.net . 